{# Jinja2 template for modals and related JS to display figures references, and tables
## Added to page templates with {% include "modal.html.jinja" %}
#}
<div class="modal" id="genModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="modalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-lg modal-dialog" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header modal-header-generic-textpage">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
        <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body" id="modal-body">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="modal" id="versionModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="modalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-lg modal-dialog" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header modal-header-generic-textpage">
        <h5 class="modal-title">Version Information</h5>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
        <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body" id="version-modal-body">
          <p>The authors of <i>Excavating Occaneechi Town</i> recognize that, while all the information recovered in an archaeological excavation may have scientific importance, it is inappropriate to display some of that information, such as photographs of human bones, in a publication meant for the general public. The original CD-ROM edition (1998) could optionally be installed as a “Professional Version,” which contained these images. That version has now been discontinued.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<script src="../../assets/js/lightgallery-all.js"></script>
<script src="../../assets/js/load-modals.js"></script>
